1
00:01:35,300 --> 00:01:39,999
=The Litchi Road=

2
00:01:42,020 --> 00:01:43,100
(Mountain Retreat Painting)

3
00:01:44,060 --> 00:01:46,980
(Twelve Years Ago)

4
00:01:55,500 --> 00:01:56,579
Watchman.

5
00:01:56,580 --> 00:01:57,810
I am Zhao Xinmin,

6
00:01:58,060 --> 00:01:59,730
a fellow townsman of Advisor Wang.

7
00:02:01,900 --> 00:02:03,850
The gentleman is receiving a guest.

8
00:02:03,940 --> 00:02:05,810
Please wait a moment.

9
00:02:06,380 --> 00:02:07,570
Thank you.

10
00:02:14,740 --> 00:02:16,259
Judging by your look,

11
00:02:16,260 --> 00:02:18,370
you're also here to ask
for Advisor Wang's help.

12
00:02:23,900 --> 00:02:25,090
Advisor Wang

13
00:02:26,100 --> 00:02:28,370
is a role model for scholars like us.

14
00:02:31,580 --> 00:02:32,770
I came

15
00:02:33,380 --> 00:02:35,770
just hoping he could give me
some feedback on my essay.

16
00:02:35,900 --> 00:02:38,010
I don't dare ask for a recommendation.

17
00:02:40,820 --> 00:02:42,050
Get out!

18
00:02:42,100 --> 00:02:43,699
Shameless! Absolutely shameless!

19
00:02:43,700 --> 00:02:45,019
You are from a noble family,

20
00:02:45,020 --> 00:02:46,579
and still stoop to this?

21
00:02:46,580 --> 00:02:48,770
Out! Get out!

22
00:02:48,900 --> 00:02:50,090
Out!

23
00:02:50,300 --> 00:02:51,490
Out!

24
00:02:55,020 --> 00:02:57,339
You are just a lowly advisor

25
00:02:57,340 --> 00:02:58,939
in the Court of Judicial Review!

26
00:02:58,940 --> 00:02:59,899
What's the big deal?

27
00:02:59,900 --> 00:03:00,779
Sir.

28
00:03:02,980 --> 00:03:04,170
Let's go.

29
00:03:13,500 --> 00:03:15,050
We're out of tea.

30
00:03:15,660 --> 00:03:17,130
I haven't gone to buy more yet.

31
00:03:21,500 --> 00:03:23,570
I brought this from home.

32
00:03:23,580 --> 00:03:24,770
Please have a taste.

33
00:03:29,860 --> 00:03:31,570
It's only been a few years,

34
00:03:31,660 --> 00:03:32,899
and you've already picked up

35
00:03:32,900 --> 00:03:34,530
the habit of giving gifts.

36
00:03:35,020 --> 00:03:37,330
Have all those books
you read been for nothing?

37
00:03:38,460 --> 00:03:39,650
I am ashamed.

38
00:03:45,540 --> 00:03:46,819
Your writing is top-tier,

39
00:03:46,820 --> 00:03:48,450
yet you live a frugal life.

40
00:03:48,540 --> 00:03:50,610
I deeply admire that.

41
00:03:51,460 --> 00:03:53,730
What brings you here today?

42
00:03:54,540 --> 00:03:56,890
I've studied harder than ever

43
00:03:56,900 --> 00:03:58,090
after failing the exam.

44
00:03:58,980 --> 00:04:00,850
I've written three essays.

45
00:04:02,060 --> 00:04:03,370
Please take a look, sir.

46
00:04:22,420 --> 00:04:23,610
Very good.

47
00:04:26,620 --> 00:04:27,810
Very good.

48
00:04:29,220 --> 00:04:30,610
Excellent.

49
00:04:30,940 --> 00:04:32,570
Writing to express your will!

50
00:04:32,900 --> 00:04:35,810
Especially the quote
about men of virtue.

51
00:04:35,820 --> 00:04:37,899
"They do not cling to life
at the cost of benevolence,

52
00:04:37,900 --> 00:04:39,970
but would sacrifice themselves for it."

53
00:04:40,820 --> 00:04:42,690
To die for virtue,
to uphold righteousness!

54
00:04:42,860 --> 00:04:44,730
Your essay shows great vision.

55
00:04:46,180 --> 00:04:47,490
You are too kind, sir.

56
00:04:47,740 --> 00:04:49,890
Sir, please take a look at this too.

57
00:04:50,380 --> 00:04:51,570
Put it away.

58
00:04:51,620 --> 00:04:54,330
Didn't you hear
what Advisor Wang just said?

59
00:04:55,300 --> 00:04:56,530
This is different.

60
00:05:03,720 --> 00:05:06,330
(Wang's Work)

61
00:05:06,940 --> 00:05:10,130
Sir, is this your painting?

62
00:05:14,540 --> 00:05:18,370
Where did you get this scroll?

63
00:05:19,060 --> 00:05:21,250
I merely stumbled upon it by chance.

64
00:05:25,100 --> 00:05:26,610
To be honest,

65
00:05:26,820 --> 00:05:30,810
a while back,
I couldn't even afford my next meal.

66
00:05:31,420 --> 00:05:33,250
I had no choice

67
00:05:33,620 --> 00:05:37,170
but to trade the painting
for a few pints of rice and flour.

68
00:05:38,500 --> 00:05:40,890
I didn't come here to
present a gift but rather

69
00:05:41,580 --> 00:05:43,170
return it to its rightful owner.

70
00:05:43,740 --> 00:05:45,890
This painting holds lofty meaning.

71
00:05:46,140 --> 00:05:49,210
Only someone as pure and modest as you

72
00:05:49,620 --> 00:05:51,090
is worthy of it.

73
00:05:51,820 --> 00:05:54,890
Your writing also matches
the spirit of this painting.

74
00:05:55,820 --> 00:05:58,570
You shall hang it up for me.

75
00:06:01,860 --> 00:06:03,050
Yes, sir.

76
00:06:15,300 --> 00:06:16,379
Zhao,

77
00:06:16,380 --> 00:06:17,570
I'll give you a boost.

78
00:06:20,340 --> 00:06:22,090
Is this really appropriate?

79
00:06:22,260 --> 00:06:23,690
Go ahead, Zhao.

80
00:06:24,060 --> 00:06:25,250
Very well.

81
00:06:25,500 --> 00:06:27,970
Yes. You have my thanks.

82
00:06:30,810 --> 00:06:31,699
Get on the ground!

83
00:06:31,700 --> 00:06:32,890
Freeze!

84
00:06:35,010 --> 00:06:35,859
Get on the ground!

85
00:06:35,860 --> 00:06:37,050
Freeze!

86
00:06:37,980 --> 00:06:39,770
Get on the ground!

87
00:06:46,180 --> 00:06:47,299
The owner of Jubao Store

88
00:06:47,300 --> 00:06:48,499
has already confessed.

89
00:06:48,500 --> 00:06:49,939
You kept consigning your paintings

90
00:06:49,940 --> 00:06:51,290
for sale at the shop.

91
00:06:52,020 --> 00:06:53,650
And if someone wanted a favor,

92
00:06:53,780 --> 00:06:54,939
you'd sell them at high prices,

93
00:06:54,940 --> 00:06:57,370
then split the profit
between the two of you.

94
00:06:57,940 --> 00:06:59,619
Now that we've caught you red-handed,

95
00:06:59,620 --> 00:07:01,050
what else is there to say?

96
00:07:01,500 --> 00:07:03,370
I lost my head for a moment.

97
00:07:04,180 --> 00:07:05,730
I made a mistake!

98
00:07:06,380 --> 00:07:07,570
It was a mistake!

99
00:08:06,060 --> 00:08:09,410
=Episode 11=

100
00:08:10,740 --> 00:08:11,970
Raise your head!

101
00:08:15,140 --> 00:08:17,050
Has anyone here

102
00:08:17,660 --> 00:08:19,810
seen a rat in the residence?

103
00:08:22,380 --> 00:08:23,339
Well?

104
00:08:23,340 --> 00:08:24,530
Anyone?

105
00:08:29,820 --> 00:08:31,050
Zhao,

106
00:08:32,460 --> 00:08:33,619
do you realize

107
00:08:33,620 --> 00:08:35,139
how arrogant the rats are

108
00:08:35,140 --> 00:08:37,739
in the Inspector's Office?

109
00:08:37,740 --> 00:08:39,659
They are bold enough
to scurry right up to me,

110
00:08:39,660 --> 00:08:41,250
just shy of speaking to me!

111
00:08:42,500 --> 00:08:44,059
Are you really blind to them,

112
00:08:44,060 --> 00:08:45,379
or just pretending not to see?

113
00:08:45,380 --> 00:08:47,410
Or are you too scared to speak up?

114
00:08:48,220 --> 00:08:50,339
Seems like you've all
joined the rats' side and

115
00:08:50,340 --> 00:08:51,670
conspired with vermin!

116
00:08:51,810 --> 00:08:52,659
We wouldn't dare.

117
00:08:52,660 --> 00:08:54,179
We wouldn't dare!

118
00:08:54,180 --> 00:08:55,499
Wouldn't dare what?

119
00:08:55,500 --> 00:08:57,170
What are you too scared of?

120
00:09:03,540 --> 00:09:04,770
Listen up.

121
00:09:05,340 --> 00:09:07,370
It won't be hard
to get to the bottom of this.

122
00:09:07,960 --> 00:09:09,099
Go.

123
00:09:09,100 --> 00:09:11,530
Bring me that Linyi slave in shackles.

124
00:09:11,740 --> 00:09:13,410
I'll interrogate him myself.

125
00:09:16,380 --> 00:09:17,229
Go on!

126
00:09:17,230 --> 00:09:20,459
That Linyi slave was taken away

127
00:09:20,460 --> 00:09:22,890
by the Litchi Envoy.

128
00:09:24,820 --> 00:09:26,339
Why would the Litchi Envoy

129
00:09:26,340 --> 00:09:28,250
take the Linyi slave?

130
00:09:29,940 --> 00:09:32,170
That Litchi Envoy is way too aggressive.

131
00:09:32,820 --> 00:09:34,170
He shouted at me.

132
00:09:34,460 --> 00:09:37,419
He wanted the document and the slave,
or there'd be bloodshed.

133
00:09:37,420 --> 00:09:39,179
He was terrifying.

134
00:09:39,180 --> 00:09:41,770
I was worried he'd bring bad luck

135
00:09:41,900 --> 00:09:43,419
to the entire residence,

136
00:09:43,420 --> 00:09:45,170
so I gave him the slave.

137
00:09:47,500 --> 00:09:49,299
I even told him deliberately

138
00:09:49,300 --> 00:09:52,050
that the Linyi slave was mute,

139
00:09:52,380 --> 00:09:53,899
so he'd let his guard down.

140
00:09:53,900 --> 00:09:55,419
That way, everything he does

141
00:09:55,420 --> 00:09:57,370
will be under our control.

142
00:10:00,020 --> 00:10:01,490
Master Zhao.

143
00:10:04,020 --> 00:10:05,210
No.

144
00:10:06,060 --> 00:10:08,130
We still need to investigate this.

145
00:10:15,140 --> 00:10:16,330
Inspector.

146
00:10:16,650 --> 00:10:17,619
Speak.

147
00:10:17,620 --> 00:10:19,210
Amita has come to visit.

148
00:10:22,780 --> 00:10:23,699
Amita.

149
00:10:23,700 --> 00:10:27,050
(Inspector's Office)

150
00:10:27,140 --> 00:10:28,410
Godfather.

151
00:10:29,420 --> 00:10:31,530
The servants said
you lost your temper again.

152
00:10:32,380 --> 00:10:33,619
These servants

153
00:10:33,620 --> 00:10:35,139
have no sense of boundaries.

154
00:10:35,140 --> 00:10:36,499
If I don't keep them in line,

155
00:10:36,500 --> 00:10:38,059
they will think I'm easy to fool.

156
00:10:38,060 --> 00:10:39,219
You should calm down.

157
00:10:39,220 --> 00:10:40,690
It's bad for your health.

158
00:10:41,020 --> 00:10:42,450
I know.

159
00:10:44,420 --> 00:10:47,170
What brings you by today?

160
00:10:47,380 --> 00:10:49,170
I heard Su Liang

161
00:10:49,180 --> 00:10:50,859
is investing in litchi transport,

162
00:10:50,860 --> 00:10:52,720
so I came to discuss it with you.

163
00:10:53,900 --> 00:10:56,299
I heard he's found riders and horses

164
00:10:56,300 --> 00:10:58,650
to do a litchi transport trial run.

165
00:10:59,140 --> 00:11:01,019
Do you think that Litchi Envoy

166
00:11:01,020 --> 00:11:02,339
might actually be capable

167
00:11:02,340 --> 00:11:03,570
of pulling this off?

168
00:11:04,180 --> 00:11:06,299
What can he possibly pull off?

169
00:11:06,300 --> 00:11:08,130
Let them fool around.

170
00:11:10,420 --> 00:11:12,339
Su Liang loves gambling
on opportunities.

171
00:11:12,340 --> 00:11:14,050
He likes high-risk and high-reward.

172
00:11:14,740 --> 00:11:15,979
If he weren't sure

173
00:11:15,980 --> 00:11:17,810
this could make money,

174
00:11:18,460 --> 00:11:20,330
he wouldn't put a coin in.

175
00:11:20,820 --> 00:11:21,699
If litchi transport

176
00:11:21,700 --> 00:11:23,379
really is a business opportunity,

177
00:11:23,380 --> 00:11:25,459
I can't let him get a head start.

178
00:11:25,460 --> 00:11:27,219
He is clearly trying to make a comeback

179
00:11:27,220 --> 00:11:28,979
and threaten my place
in the Association.

180
00:11:28,980 --> 00:11:30,450
I have to crush him.

181
00:11:30,540 --> 00:11:31,770
I'm investing in it.

182
00:11:33,640 --> 00:11:34,830
Amita.

183
00:11:35,580 --> 00:11:38,410
Don't get involved
with the litchi business.

184
00:11:38,700 --> 00:11:40,739
There's no way I'll let those litchis

185
00:11:40,740 --> 00:11:42,410
get to Chang'an.

186
00:11:43,020 --> 00:11:44,210
Why not?

187
00:11:44,700 --> 00:11:45,890
Think about it.

188
00:11:46,100 --> 00:11:47,819
If those fresh litchis

189
00:11:47,820 --> 00:11:49,659
actually make it to Chang'an,

190
00:11:49,660 --> 00:11:52,570
and His Majesty likes the taste,

191
00:11:52,620 --> 00:11:53,970
he'll naturally ask,

192
00:11:53,980 --> 00:11:55,930
"Why weren't they delivered before?"

193
00:11:56,460 --> 00:11:57,539
When that happens,

194
00:11:57,540 --> 00:11:59,250
how am I supposed to answer?

195
00:11:59,780 --> 00:12:00,659
Also,

196
00:12:00,660 --> 00:12:05,130
Lingnan has always
been a place for the exiled.

197
00:12:05,380 --> 00:12:07,490
Even birds won't linger here.

198
00:12:07,500 --> 00:12:08,979
And it's exactly because of that

199
00:12:08,980 --> 00:12:12,930
that I get to live like a king.

200
00:12:13,060 --> 00:12:14,059
But if those litchis

201
00:12:14,060 --> 00:12:15,770
really make it to Chang'an,

202
00:12:15,980 --> 00:12:17,690
everything changes.

203
00:12:18,180 --> 00:12:19,699
Lingnan will turn into

204
00:12:19,700 --> 00:12:21,170
a juicy piece of meat.

205
00:12:21,180 --> 00:12:23,610
This place will start thriving.

206
00:12:23,820 --> 00:12:25,450
And the people coming and going

207
00:12:25,620 --> 00:12:27,970
will all be big shots from Chang'an.

208
00:12:28,700 --> 00:12:30,130
Then,

209
00:12:30,140 --> 00:12:32,659
I am nothing more than a rooster

210
00:12:32,660 --> 00:12:34,339
stealing a few grains of rice.

211
00:12:34,340 --> 00:12:36,090
But those folks from Chang'an?

212
00:12:36,140 --> 00:12:38,299
They are all avaricious beasts.

213
00:12:38,300 --> 00:12:40,899
They won't just steal our rice,

214
00:12:40,900 --> 00:12:43,330
they will swallow us whole.

215
00:12:43,380 --> 00:12:44,770
When that day comes,

216
00:12:44,820 --> 00:12:46,370
Lingnan won't be

217
00:12:46,700 --> 00:12:49,330
a place we can call home.

218
00:12:50,020 --> 00:12:52,570
It'll be our graveyard.

219
00:12:53,020 --> 00:12:54,819
Godfather, you are truly far-sighted.

220
00:12:54,820 --> 00:12:56,930
I only thought about
getting ahead in business.

221
00:12:57,540 --> 00:12:59,610
I didn't realize that

222
00:12:59,740 --> 00:13:01,250
it could lie a deadly trap.

223
00:13:03,140 --> 00:13:05,130
Su Liang probably sees it too.

224
00:13:09,540 --> 00:13:10,419
He is trying to open up

225
00:13:10,420 --> 00:13:12,010
a trade route to Chang'an.

226
00:13:14,500 --> 00:13:16,179
Quite the ambition.

227
00:13:16,180 --> 00:13:17,370
Indeed.

228
00:13:17,860 --> 00:13:19,970
Do you think he is really capable of it?

229
00:13:21,460 --> 00:13:24,539
Litchi transport costs a fortune.

230
00:13:24,540 --> 00:13:25,899
With his resources alone,

231
00:13:25,900 --> 00:13:27,410
can he even handle it?

232
00:13:28,860 --> 00:13:31,290
One more thing, Amita.

233
00:13:31,340 --> 00:13:33,050
Remember what I say.

234
00:13:33,180 --> 00:13:34,739
In this world,

235
00:13:34,740 --> 00:13:37,939
it's nearly hard
to make something succeed.

236
00:13:37,940 --> 00:13:39,890
But to ruin something?

237
00:13:44,260 --> 00:13:45,299
Just think about it.

238
00:13:45,300 --> 00:13:47,370
What if Li Shande doesn't have horses?

239
00:13:47,420 --> 00:13:48,690
Then what?

240
00:13:50,820 --> 00:13:52,010
I see.

241
00:13:56,700 --> 00:13:58,490
Dear, are you hungry yet?

242
00:13:59,580 --> 00:14:00,770
No appetite.

243
00:14:04,780 --> 00:14:06,610
How about some sweet soup instead?

244
00:14:07,500 --> 00:14:08,690
You have it.

245
00:14:17,700 --> 00:14:19,570
That old fox...

246
00:14:19,860 --> 00:14:21,419
I think he's found out

247
00:14:21,420 --> 00:14:23,510
about me embezzling
the rat control funds.

248
00:14:24,740 --> 00:14:26,370
Did he get proof?

249
00:14:27,300 --> 00:14:28,819
Thankfully, I planned ahead.

250
00:14:28,820 --> 00:14:30,970
I sent the Linyi slave away.

251
00:14:31,620 --> 00:14:34,650
I cut the problem off at its root.

252
00:14:34,860 --> 00:14:38,170
Now, he has no trail to follow.

253
00:14:38,380 --> 00:14:39,859
You're brilliant, my love.

254
00:14:39,860 --> 00:14:41,890
That old fox is no match for you.

255
00:14:43,020 --> 00:14:44,370
You flatter me.

256
00:14:45,020 --> 00:14:46,259
He is a cunning one.

257
00:14:46,260 --> 00:14:48,050
How else could he become Inspector?

258
00:14:49,820 --> 00:14:51,010
That man...

259
00:14:53,180 --> 00:14:56,019
Sometimes, he acts like a fool,

260
00:14:56,020 --> 00:14:57,259
dense as a pig.

261
00:14:57,260 --> 00:15:00,570
Even talking to him feels pointless.

262
00:15:00,860 --> 00:15:02,130
But sometimes,

263
00:15:02,380 --> 00:15:04,329
he is as shrewd as a monkey.

264
00:15:04,330 --> 00:15:05,520
Take today, for example.

265
00:15:05,980 --> 00:15:08,659
The steward already
had all the rats poisoned.

266
00:15:08,660 --> 00:15:10,259
There was no way he saw one last night.

267
00:15:10,260 --> 00:15:12,179
Yet, he insisted he did.

268
00:15:12,180 --> 00:15:13,699
He just wanted to use it

269
00:15:13,700 --> 00:15:15,490
to rattle me a little.

270
00:15:16,780 --> 00:15:19,370
As if I, the Chief Scribe,

271
00:15:20,180 --> 00:15:22,410
don't do the steward's job as well.

272
00:15:22,540 --> 00:15:23,779
I skim a little off the top.

273
00:15:23,780 --> 00:15:25,219
That's only fair.

274
00:15:25,220 --> 00:15:26,019
Look at him.

275
00:15:26,020 --> 00:15:27,179
He is treating all of Lingnan

276
00:15:27,180 --> 00:15:28,379
like his backyard.

277
00:15:28,380 --> 00:15:30,039
And I can't even build

278
00:15:30,040 --> 00:15:30,859
a little garden.

279
00:15:30,860 --> 00:15:33,979
I am the Chief Scribe
of the Inspector's Office!

280
00:15:33,980 --> 00:15:35,979
Skimming a bit from the rat funds

281
00:15:35,980 --> 00:15:37,930
even sounds pathetic.

282
00:15:38,500 --> 00:15:41,330
Even if he starts suspecting you,

283
00:15:42,300 --> 00:15:44,490
he wouldn't dare touch you.

284
00:15:45,620 --> 00:15:47,699
Without your help,

285
00:15:47,700 --> 00:15:50,170
he can't even write a loyalty pledge.

286
00:15:50,380 --> 00:15:51,299
The man is illiterate.

287
00:15:51,300 --> 00:15:52,579
That much isn't an act.

288
00:15:52,580 --> 00:15:54,050
True enough.

289
00:15:54,260 --> 00:15:55,730
He used to be a pirate.

290
00:15:55,780 --> 00:15:56,699
He can barely

291
00:15:56,700 --> 00:15:57,930
recognize his own name.

292
00:15:58,340 --> 00:16:01,290
That day, he put on such a show.

293
00:16:01,940 --> 00:16:03,299
However, he didn't even know

294
00:16:03,300 --> 00:16:05,850
how to write the word "loyalty."

295
00:16:07,540 --> 00:16:09,299
He still tried to save face.

296
00:16:09,300 --> 00:16:10,459
"Let me test you."

297
00:16:10,460 --> 00:16:12,210
He even made me recite it for him.

298
00:16:13,500 --> 00:16:15,819
Hopeless uneducated.

299
00:16:15,820 --> 00:16:17,530
If I ever resign, he will see

300
00:16:17,580 --> 00:16:18,539
that the whole office

301
00:16:18,540 --> 00:16:19,899
rests on my shoulders.

302
00:16:19,900 --> 00:16:21,459
Without me, it all falls apart.

303
00:16:21,460 --> 00:16:22,650
Indeed.

304
00:16:23,340 --> 00:16:27,179
All your talents are wasted

305
00:16:27,180 --> 00:16:28,770
in the Inspector's Office.

306
00:16:31,300 --> 00:16:35,250
Such brilliance,
met with such poor fortune.

307
00:16:35,620 --> 00:16:38,699
All I do every day is manage chickens

308
00:16:38,700 --> 00:16:41,259
and rats.

309
00:16:41,260 --> 00:16:42,779
I have all these skills,

310
00:16:42,780 --> 00:16:46,090
but I don't even
get to use a tenth of them.

311
00:16:46,820 --> 00:16:48,410
With your talent,

312
00:16:48,580 --> 00:16:50,219
you could serve the emperor

313
00:16:50,220 --> 00:16:52,290
using only half your strength.

314
00:16:52,580 --> 00:16:54,290
If you gave it your all,

315
00:16:54,460 --> 00:16:56,370
you'd rule the world.

316
00:16:57,900 --> 00:16:59,090
Careful.

317
00:16:59,340 --> 00:17:01,250
Words like that can't be spoken lightly.

318
00:17:04,380 --> 00:17:06,299
But, you nearly made it

319
00:17:06,300 --> 00:17:08,210
to the top of the list in Lingnan.

320
00:17:08,580 --> 00:17:10,259
Even if you had gone to Chang'an,

321
00:17:10,260 --> 00:17:12,290
you wouldn't have lost
to those officials.

322
00:17:21,740 --> 00:17:22,930
Back then,

323
00:17:23,620 --> 00:17:24,539
if my father hadn't

324
00:17:24,540 --> 00:17:26,130
stopped you from going to Chang'an,

325
00:17:26,780 --> 00:17:29,050
you'd have made a name
for yourself long ago.

326
00:17:37,500 --> 00:17:38,810
For me...

327
00:17:42,300 --> 00:17:44,130
For me, my dear,

328
00:17:44,700 --> 00:17:47,730
fame and fortune mean nothing.

329
00:17:48,660 --> 00:17:49,859
Staying for you

330
00:17:49,860 --> 00:17:51,330
will never be my regret.

331
00:17:51,500 --> 00:17:53,890
Whenever we sit and talk like this,

332
00:17:54,380 --> 00:17:56,890
my heart always feels lighter.

333
00:18:00,340 --> 00:18:01,970
So, is the rat matter

334
00:18:02,220 --> 00:18:03,539
settled now?

335
00:18:03,540 --> 00:18:04,730
It is.

336
00:18:08,140 --> 00:18:09,659
Thanks to that Litchi Envoy

337
00:18:09,660 --> 00:18:11,010
