daughters of grace.

567
00:26:51,420 --> 00:26:53,859
Now that I've seen her in person,

568
00:26:53,860 --> 00:26:56,330
she's basically a goddess from heaven.

569
00:26:56,900 --> 00:26:58,779
Back in Chang'an, I heard the legends.

570
00:26:58,780 --> 00:27:00,250
The Flower of the Hu Women,

571
00:27:00,740 --> 00:27:01,939
the overlord of the South Seas,

572
00:27:01,940 --> 00:27:03,139
the merchant of Lingnan.

573
00:27:03,140 --> 00:27:04,299
I thought it was

574
00:27:04,300 --> 00:27:05,490
three different people.

575
00:27:05,740 --> 00:27:07,610
Turns out, it's all her.

576
00:27:08,420 --> 00:27:10,259
If Li Yannian ever saw you,

577
00:27:10,260 --> 00:27:12,570
he'd rewrite "Song of a Fair Maiden".

578
00:27:12,580 --> 00:27:13,979
"Down south lives a beauty."

579
00:27:13,980 --> 00:27:16,730
Miss, your beauty is unmatched
in the entire nation.

580
00:27:17,780 --> 00:27:18,899
You flatter me.

581
00:27:18,900 --> 00:27:19,939
My godfather mentioned

582
00:27:19,940 --> 00:27:21,979
the Right Chancellor was sending
an envoy here...

583
00:27:21,980 --> 00:27:23,819
I didn't expect him to be this young

584
00:27:23,820 --> 00:27:25,210
and so refined.

585
00:27:25,700 --> 00:27:26,499
Not at all.

586
00:27:26,500 --> 00:27:27,259
Not at all.

587
00:27:27,260 --> 00:27:29,570
Refined? I am utterly flattered.

588
00:27:30,780 --> 00:27:32,850
But if you hand out
compliments like that...

589
00:27:33,940 --> 00:27:36,459
I'll throw a banquet
at Qifeng Pavilion tonight.

590
00:27:36,460 --> 00:27:39,170
We can get to know each other better.

591
00:27:40,500 --> 00:27:41,379
What a shame.

592
00:27:41,380 --> 00:27:43,339
It just so happens I'm busy with work.

593
00:27:43,340 --> 00:27:44,339
Maybe another time?

594
00:27:44,340 --> 00:27:45,570
How about tomorrow?

595
00:27:48,300 --> 00:27:49,930
Tomorrow it is.

596
00:27:50,100 --> 00:27:51,290
Tomorrow is a good day.

597
00:27:52,220 --> 00:27:55,090
Great. I'll be waiting, miss.

598
00:27:57,660 --> 00:27:58,850
Su.

599
00:27:58,860 --> 00:28:00,899
How is it going
with the horses and riders?

600
00:28:00,900 --> 00:28:02,690
Did you manage to hire them?

601
00:28:03,940 --> 00:28:06,210
I was just about to report.

602
00:28:06,940 --> 00:28:09,299
Amita's been stirring up

603
00:28:09,300 --> 00:28:10,650
trouble at the market.

604
00:28:10,780 --> 00:28:12,290
She is jacking up horse prices.

605
00:28:12,980 --> 00:28:16,059
Is this the same Amita

606
00:28:16,060 --> 00:28:17,619
who snatched your spices?

607
00:28:17,620 --> 00:28:18,459
The very same.

608
00:28:18,460 --> 00:28:20,210
What is she after our horses?

609
00:28:20,540 --> 00:28:21,739
How is she involved

610
00:28:21,740 --> 00:28:23,210
in this matter?

611
00:28:23,380 --> 00:28:24,570
Don't forget,

612
00:28:24,820 --> 00:28:27,050
Amita's godfather is He Youguang.

613
00:28:27,100 --> 00:28:28,819
If you really ship the litchis

614
00:28:28,820 --> 00:28:30,299
out of Lingnan,

615
00:28:30,300 --> 00:28:34,210
the father and daughter's little fortune

616
00:28:34,220 --> 00:28:36,370
won't keep rolling in.

617
00:28:36,460 --> 00:28:39,770
Could you maybe think of a way

618
00:28:39,900 --> 00:28:41,490
to buy some fine horses from Amita?

619
00:28:43,060 --> 00:28:45,690
Amita and I never see eye to eye.

620
00:28:45,780 --> 00:28:47,499
If I go smiling at her,

621
00:28:47,500 --> 00:28:49,450
she will think I'm a weasel

622
00:28:49,860 --> 00:28:52,130
dropping in on a henhouse.

623
00:28:52,300 --> 00:28:54,130
She will become unbelievably ruthless.

624
00:28:54,700 --> 00:28:55,699
That idiom,

625
00:28:55,700 --> 00:28:56,939
while technically wrong,

626
00:28:56,940 --> 00:28:59,210
gets the point across just fine.

627
00:29:01,900 --> 00:29:03,530
How about I go instead?

628
00:29:04,140 --> 00:29:06,419
His Majesty's grace
reaches all four corners.

629
00:29:06,420 --> 00:29:07,419
I act on his behalf.

630
00:29:07,420 --> 00:29:08,539
She can't exactly say no.

631
00:29:08,540 --> 00:29:09,730
Good.

632
00:29:11,100 --> 00:29:14,530
But let me give you a heads-up.

633
00:29:15,180 --> 00:29:18,139
Amita has a cold heart

634
00:29:18,140 --> 00:29:19,930
and a twisted mind.

635
00:29:20,140 --> 00:29:23,210
But, you have strong limbs

636
00:29:23,540 --> 00:29:25,330
and a simple brain.

637
00:29:25,620 --> 00:29:28,459
So go ahead and ask
for a ridiculous number.

638
00:29:28,460 --> 00:29:30,730
Try to get as many horses as you can.

639
00:29:31,180 --> 00:29:34,250
Even if she slashes the number in half,

640
00:29:34,380 --> 00:29:36,090
it will still be

641
00:29:36,140 --> 00:29:38,330
enough for this transport.

642
00:29:39,500 --> 00:29:40,730
Did you get

643
00:29:40,740 --> 00:29:43,130
what I just said?

644
00:29:45,900 --> 00:29:47,090
Got it.

645
00:30:11,340 --> 00:30:13,690
Make a few merchants lock the price in.

646
00:30:13,860 --> 00:30:15,770
No other merchant groups
can take that hit.

647
00:30:16,060 --> 00:30:17,250
Yes.

648
00:30:20,340 --> 00:30:21,530
Leader.

649
00:30:23,020 --> 00:30:24,210
I'm fine.

650
00:30:25,300 --> 00:30:26,490
Thank you for the hard work.

651
00:30:28,140 --> 00:30:29,539
This Tang nobleman

652
00:30:29,540 --> 00:30:30,730
came to see me too?

653
00:30:31,020 --> 00:30:32,250
You must be the leader.

654
00:30:33,660 --> 00:30:35,930
I am the Litchi Envoy from Chang'an.

655
00:30:39,180 --> 00:30:41,139
I'd like to ask you

656
00:30:41,140 --> 00:30:43,370
to sell me a batch of fine horses.

657
00:30:45,220 --> 00:30:48,730
So, you are that Litchi Envoy.

658
00:30:50,260 --> 00:30:52,130
You've caused me quite a bit of trouble.

659
00:30:52,140 --> 00:30:53,739
I haven't even settled our old scores,

660
00:30:53,740 --> 00:30:55,099
and now you show up at my door

661
00:30:55,100 --> 00:30:56,570
to talk business?

662
00:30:57,420 --> 00:31:00,139
I do apologize
for everything that happened.

663
00:31:00,140 --> 00:31:02,219
I am working for His Majesty,

664
00:31:02,220 --> 00:31:03,459
and there are things

665
00:31:03,460 --> 00:31:04,970
beyond my control.

666
00:31:05,100 --> 00:31:06,330
I'm just being honest.

667
00:31:06,980 --> 00:31:08,339
So this time,

668
00:31:08,340 --> 00:31:10,259
I've come to pay you properly

669
00:31:10,260 --> 00:31:12,130
for 130 fine horses.

670
00:31:12,300 --> 00:31:13,850
Please help me out.

671
00:31:15,540 --> 00:31:18,210
What a money-grubbing official you are.

672
00:31:21,540 --> 00:31:22,930
As the saying goes,

673
00:31:23,020 --> 00:31:25,210
you are all cut from the same cloth.

674
00:31:26,100 --> 00:31:28,570
But you are the worst of them all.

675
00:31:29,380 --> 00:31:31,450
Do you need that many
for a few litchis?

676
00:31:31,540 --> 00:31:32,739
I'm not corrupt.

677
00:31:32,740 --> 00:31:34,579
I have it all planned out.

678
00:31:34,580 --> 00:31:36,299
I designed four separate routes.

679
00:31:36,300 --> 00:31:37,920
The first goes through the Mei Pass.

680
00:31:37,920 --> 00:31:40,920
The second takes the West Capital Circuit.
That's the closest to the capital.

681
00:31:40,920 --> 00:31:43,139
The third heads north, crossing the Yangtze.

682
00:31:43,140 --> 00:31:45,210
The fourth is also by water.

683
00:31:45,500 --> 00:31:46,379
Each route needs

684
00:31:46,380 --> 00:31:49,219
fifteen transfer points.

685
00:31:49,220 --> 00:31:50,579
So that's sixty

686
00:31:50,580 --> 00:31:51,979
transfer points in total.

687
00:31:51,980 --> 00:31:53,179
And each transfer point

688
00:31:53,180 --> 00:31:54,299
needs horses,

689
00:31:54,300 --> 00:31:55,459
boats, and riders.

690
00:31:55,460 --> 00:31:56,259
That's why I need

691
00:31:56,260 --> 00:31:58,090
130 fine horses.

692
00:31:59,260 --> 00:32:00,770
Even so,

693
00:32:01,060 --> 00:32:02,259
with losses included,

694
00:32:02,260 --> 00:32:03,770
100 horses would be enough.

695
00:32:04,180 --> 00:32:04,979
Why did you open with

696
00:32:04,980 --> 00:32:06,370
a request for 130?

697
00:32:07,980 --> 00:32:10,010
Well, I was just accounting for

698
00:32:11,060 --> 00:32:12,770
the bargaining losses too.

699
00:32:16,220 --> 00:32:18,010
At least you are honest.

700
00:32:18,900 --> 00:32:19,899
I bought a batch

701
00:32:19,900 --> 00:32:21,410
for the association.

702
00:32:22,460 --> 00:32:23,139
But, those horses

703
00:32:23,140 --> 00:32:24,619
are already out delivering cargo.

704
00:32:24,620 --> 00:32:26,219
They won't be back anytime soon.

705
00:32:26,220 --> 00:32:27,339
So I'm afraid

706
00:32:27,340 --> 00:32:28,850
I really can't help you.

707
00:32:29,380 --> 00:32:30,819
Surely not every last one of them

708
00:32:30,820 --> 00:32:32,019
is out on the road?

709
00:32:32,020 --> 00:32:33,059
There has been a rush

710
00:32:33,060 --> 00:32:35,410
of shipments at the docks,
and not enough transport.

711
00:32:35,660 --> 00:32:37,690
We truly can't spare even a single horse.

712
00:32:37,780 --> 00:32:38,659
I know this is

713
00:32:38,660 --> 00:32:40,179
a rush job given by His Majesty.

714
00:32:40,180 --> 00:32:41,019
So, don't waste

715
00:32:41,020 --> 00:32:42,250
any more time with me.

716
00:32:45,140 --> 00:32:46,490
But there is one thing

717
00:32:47,820 --> 00:32:49,490
you might want to know.

718
00:32:50,500 --> 00:32:53,090
I don't mind letting go
of the litchi garden.

719
00:32:53,140 --> 00:32:54,739
But the debt it owes

720
00:32:54,740 --> 00:32:55,930
must be repaid.

721
00:32:56,020 --> 00:32:57,410
We Hu people

722
00:32:57,980 --> 00:33:00,699
always repay kindness

723
00:33:00,700 --> 00:33:02,290
and settle our debts.

724
00:33:05,420 --> 00:33:07,610
The money was borrowed
when the irises bloomed.

725
00:33:08,740 --> 00:33:11,090
If it's not repaid
before the petals fall,

726
00:33:12,340 --> 00:33:14,050
we'll chop the debtor's hand off.

727
00:33:14,660 --> 00:33:16,530
It's too hot in Lingnan.

728
00:33:17,020 --> 00:33:19,810
These irises don't grow too well.

729
00:33:20,020 --> 00:33:22,810
They probably won't last many more days.

730
00:33:23,620 --> 00:33:24,810
Leader,

731
00:33:25,580 --> 00:33:27,730
the Dong people from the garden

732
00:33:27,860 --> 00:33:30,730
still need to help me
transport the litchis.

733
00:33:30,900 --> 00:33:32,019
Can I beg you

734
00:33:32,020 --> 00:33:33,370
to let them off the hook?

735
00:33:34,700 --> 00:33:36,099
As a leader,

736
00:33:36,100 --> 00:33:36,659
I must consider

737
00:33:36,660 --> 00:33:38,250
the Hu merchants' interests.

738
00:33:38,980 --> 00:33:40,379
Even if I let them go,

739
00:33:40,380 --> 00:33:41,939
the others in charge won't agree.

740
00:33:41,940 --> 00:33:43,530
I can vouch for them.

741
00:33:43,620 --> 00:33:46,219
After the sixth month of the year,
they will pay it back.

742
00:33:46,220 --> 00:33:47,410
How about that?

743
00:33:48,220 --> 00:33:50,019
You sure you will live till then

744
00:33:50,020 --> 00:33:51,450
to see it happen?

745
00:33:58,060 --> 00:34:00,059
Leader, you mentioned

746
00:34:00,060 --> 00:34:02,419
the iris blooming.

747
00:34:02,420 --> 00:34:04,859
If the debt is to be paid
before it withers.

748
00:34:04,860 --> 00:34:05,659
What if

749
00:34:05,660 --> 00:34:07,139
the flower doesn't wither?

750
00:34:07,140 --> 00:34:09,059
Does that mean we can

751
00:34:09,060 --> 00:34:10,250
delay the repayment?

752
00:34:10,460 --> 00:34:11,419
Could I take it home

753
00:34:11,420 --> 00:34:13,010
and tend to it?

754
00:34:13,460 --> 00:34:14,819
Do you think you can save it?

755
00:34:14,820 --> 00:34:16,010
I can.

756
00:34:16,900 --> 00:34:18,090
Let me take a look.

757
00:34:18,980 --> 00:34:19,939
When it comes to flowers,

758
00:34:19,940 --> 00:34:21,219
if they're in my hands,

759
00:34:21,220 --> 00:34:22,650
they won't suffer.

760
00:34:25,900 --> 00:34:27,250
Let me take it and try.

761
00:34:29,700 --> 00:34:30,939
And if it dies?

762
00:34:30,940 --> 00:34:32,410
Punish me however you want.

763
00:34:34,460 --> 00:34:35,739
Now, is there any wiggle room

764
00:34:35,740 --> 00:34:37,290
with the horse deal?

765
00:34:37,860 --> 00:34:39,850
I already agreed to one thing.

766
00:34:40,500 --> 00:34:41,970
Don't push your luck.

767
00:34:43,020 --> 00:34:44,210
See him out.

768
00:34:44,420 --> 00:34:45,610
Yes.

769
00:34:47,860 --> 00:34:49,890
Envoy Li, this way.

770
00:34:50,140 --> 00:34:51,650
I'll take the flower with me.

771
00:34:56,940 --> 00:34:57,619
This Litchi Envoy

772
00:34:57,620 --> 00:34:58,859
should know his place.

773
00:34:58,860 --> 00:35:00,019
He can barely help himself,

774
00:35:00,020 --> 00:35:01,690
yet he still worries about the Dong people.

775
00:35:03,060 --> 00:35:04,339
I don't think he is

776
00:35:04,340 --> 00:35:06,970
as devious as my godfather claims.

777
00:35:08,180 --> 00:35:10,090
He actually seems kind of dumb.

778
00:35:11,940 --> 00:35:12,979
Unlike the other

779
00:35:12,980 --> 00:35:14,170
the Tang officials.

780
00:35:16,020 --> 00:35:18,979
True integrity may look naive,
and true skill, a little dumb.

781
00:35:18,980 --> 00:35:20,410
Maybe he's just faking it.

782
00:35:22,820 --> 00:35:24,450
There is an old Hu proverb.

783
00:35:25,180 --> 00:35:26,970
"Camels carry loads,

784
00:35:27,420 --> 00:35:29,090
but eagles are meant to fly."

785
00:35:30,340 --> 00:35:32,570
He might actually have some real talent.

786
00:35:33,660 --> 00:35:36,290
With the right help,

787
00:35:37,300 --> 00:35:38,890
this might not be impossible.

788
00:35:40,500 --> 00:35:43,010
Are you tempted, Leader?

789
00:35:45,460 --> 00:35:47,250
It's just business.

790
00:35:48,380 --> 00:35:50,330
I won't go against
my godfather's interests.

791
00:36:13,660 --> 00:36:15,570
Why aren't you eating or drinking now?

792
00:36:15,860 --> 00:36:16,979
Fussing over flowers

793
00:36:16,980 --> 00:36:18,370
and forgetting to rest?

794
00:36:18,580 --> 00:36:20,210
Rest?

795
00:36:21,420 --> 00:36:23,810
I'm just like
this wilted flower in the jar,

796
00:36:24,380 --> 00:36:25,930
struggling to stay alive.

797
00:36:26,700 --> 00:36:27,899
Didn't you already get

798
00:36:27,900 --> 00:36:29,370
the funding to start the trial?

799
00:36:29,900 --> 00:36:31,210
Something came up?

800
00:36:34,460 --> 00:36:35,499
Ever since I became

801
00:36:35,500 --> 00:36:37,450
the Litchi Envoy,

802
00:36:38,980 --> 00:36:40,659
Chang'an doesn't care,

803
00:36:40,660 --> 00:36:42,170
and Lingnan won't listen.

804
00:36:43,460 --> 00:36:44,539
Only Su and Tong

805
00:36:44,540 --> 00:36:46,930
have given me any real help.

806
00:36:47,340 --> 00:36:49,690
Finally Su lent me money.

807
00:36:50,020 --> 00:36:51,810
Then, Amita snatched up the horses.

808
00:36:52,180 --> 00:36:53,490
And Tong,

809
00:36:53,540 --> 00:36:55,130
who helped me pick litchis,

810
00:36:55,460 --> 00:36:57,530
is being hunt down by Amita for debts.

811
00:36:59,020 --> 00:37:00,210
Amita?

812
00:37:03,380 --> 00:37:05,450
Even my brother-in-law's
annoyed by her.

813
00:37:06,060 --> 00:37:07,410
What do you mean "even"?

814
00:37:07,940 --> 00:37:09,059
You know her?

815
00:37:09,060 --> 00:37:11,370
Not me.

816
00:37:11,740 --> 00:37:12,930
Ma Guiyun does.

817
00:37:14,860 --> 00:37:16,579
Ma Guiyun's next task

818
00:37:16,580 --> 00:37:18,210
is to get close to Amita.

819
00:37:19,540 --> 00:37:20,970
Let's not talk about that now.

820
00:37:21,340 --> 00:37:22,570
You mentioned

821
00:37:22,740 --> 00:37:24,610
Amita had taken your horses?

822
00:37:25,660 --> 00:37:26,850
Not really.

823
00:37:27,340 --> 00:37:28,730
I went to the stables.

824
00:37:28,900 --> 00:37:30,219
I think it was He Youguang

825
00:37:30,220 --> 00:37:32,850
who told her not to give them to you.

826
00:37:34,260 --> 00:37:35,419
Then, I don't get it.

827
00:37:35,420 --> 00:37:38,659
They are fine sending rare treasures

828
00:37:38,660 --> 00:37:39,899
from Lingnan to Chang'an,

829
00:37:39,900 --> 00:37:41,499
but why can't they tolerate

830
00:37:41,500 --> 00:37:44,410
a few litchis going up north?

831
00:37:44,580 --> 00:37:45,499
Rare treasures

832
00:37:45,500 --> 00:37:47,250
go to the Right Chancellor.

833
00:37:47,260 --> 00:37:49,130
That is their golden ticket.

834
00:37:49,500 --> 00:37:51,459
Litchis go to His Majesty.

835
00:37:51,460 --> 00:37:53,050
That's someone else's win.

836
00:37:53,380 --> 00:37:54,619
Those two have had

837
00:37:54,620 --> 00:37:55,979
the Lingnan pie to themselves.

838
00:37:55,980 --> 00:37:57,619
They are not about to share it.

839
00:37:57,620 --> 00:37:58,859
I don't know politics,

840
00:37:58,860 --> 00:37:59,899
or how the world works.

841
00:37:59,900 --> 00:38:01,410
I just do my job.

842
00:38:03,260 --> 00:38:03,979
Tomorrow I'll ask

843
00:38:03,980 --> 00:38:05,290
He Youguang for horses.

844
00:38:05,380 --> 00:38:06,659
It won't work.

845
00:38:06,660 --> 00:38:08,699
He will make up an excuse
and brush you off.

846
00:38:08,700 --> 00:38:09,739
Then, what do I do?

847
00:38:09,740 --> 00:38:10,539
Without horses,

848
00:38:10,540 --> 00:38:12,099
I can't run the experiment.

849
00:38:12,100 --> 00:38:14,090
And if I can't run it, I die.

850
00:38:18,580 --> 00:38:19,850
What are you laughing at?

851
00:38:20,460 --> 00:38:22,170
You still have me!

852
00:38:22,740 --> 00:38:23,859
Who am I?

853
00:38:23,860 --> 00:38:25,530
I'm Ma Guiyun!

854
00:38:26,100 --> 00:38:28,130
Just leave it to me to pull some strings

855
00:38:29,220 --> 00:38:30,650
and get it done for you.

856
00:38:34,860 --> 00:38:36,019
You don't believe me?

857
00:38:36,020 --> 00:38:38,250
In a few days, I'll have Amita

858
00:38:39,220 --> 00:38:40,779
stand before you, all prim, proper,

859
00:38:40,780 --> 00:38:41,819
and respectful,

860
00:38:41,820 --> 00:38:43,419
with hundreds of fine horses lined up

861
00:38:43,420 --> 00:38:45,130
for you to pick from.

862
00:38:47,660 --> 00:38:48,850
Come on, eat.

863
00:39:05,100 --> 00:39:10,690
(Wind)

864
00:39:11,260 --> 00:39:13,250
Guiyun, sorry to keep you waiting.

865
00:39:15,380 --> 00:39:17,459
With how busy you are
with the association,

866
00:39:17,460 --> 00:39:19,330
it's my honor just to be able

867
00:39:19,340 --> 00:39:20,930
to have a word with you.

868
00:39:21,340 --> 00:39:23,810
What's a short wait compared to that?

869
00:39:23,860 --> 00:39:25,850
Please, after you.

870
00:39:28,140 --> 00:39:30,250
Truth is, I don't like socializing.

871
00:39:30,500 --> 00:39:32,650
Unless it's a banquet for business,

872
00:39:33,300 --> 00:39:35,930
I don't attend any unrelated gatherings.

873
00:39:36,540 --> 00:39:37,970
But Guiyun,

874
00:39:38,060 --> 00:39:40,090
you've come all the way from Chang'an.

875
00:39:40,380 --> 00:39:41,419
If I didn't come in person

876
00:39:41,420 --> 00:39:42,699
to tell you myself,

877
00:39:42,700 --> 00:39:45,290
you might think I was brushing you off.

878
00:39:46,220 --> 00:39:48,450
I appreciate your honesty.

879
00:39:48,980 --> 00:39:49,819
Now I understand

880
00:39:49,820 --> 00:39:51,650
your temperament and ways.

881
00:39:51,740 --> 00:39:54,930
I won't invite you lightly in the future.

882
00:39:55,780 --> 00:39:57,210
I'm not here today

883
00:39:57,460 --> 00:40:00,050
to exchange sweet nothings.

884
00:40:00,380 --> 00:40:01,570
I wanted

885
00:40:02,380 --> 00:40:04,650
to give you a gift.

886
00:40:04,820 --> 00:40:05,939
Guiyun,

887
00:40:05,940 --> 00:40:07,530
you shouldn't have.

888
00:40:07,860 --> 00:40:09,650
What I want to give you

889
00:40:10,420 --> 00:40:12,090
is a suggestion.

890
00:40:12,380 --> 00:40:13,539
I heard the Litchi Envoy

891
00:40:13,540 --> 00:40:15,170
is in need of fine horses.

892
00:40:15,540 --> 00:40:17,259
And all the good ones in the market

893
00:40:17,260 --> 00:40:19,330
have ended up in your hands.

894
00:40:20,220 --> 00:40:21,770
My advice is...

895
00:40:23,900 --> 00:40:25,090
Let him have them.

896
00:40:26,580 --> 00:40:32,419
You came today to put up
a good word for that Litchi Envoy?

897
00:40:32,420 --> 00:40:33,730
Of course not.

898
00:40:34,980 --> 00:40:36,099
Though we both come

899
00:40:36,100 --> 00:40:37,850
from Chang'an,

900
00:40:37,900 --> 00:40:39,610
our missions are different.

901
00:40:40,020 --> 00:40:41,770
I serve the Right Chancellor.

902
00:40:41,940 --> 00:40:43,419
Why would I speak on behalf

903
00:40:43,420 --> 00:40:44,610
of a Litchi Envoy?

904
00:40:45,380 --> 00:40:46,339
We just happen to be

905
00:40:46,340 --> 00:40:47,810
staying at the same inn.

906
00:40:48,260 --> 00:40:49,530
And by chance,

907
00:40:50,100 --> 00:40:51,419
I saw him going over

908
00:40:51,420 --> 00:40:52,970
Lingnan's accounts.

909
00:40:53,700 --> 00:40:55,259
He is just a Litchi Envoy,

910
00:40:55,260 --> 00:40:57,290
and he dares to audit the ledgers?

911
00:40:57,340 --> 00:40:59,370
He clearly doesn't know his place.

912
00:41:03,580 --> 00:41:05,410
You shouldn't underestimate him.

913
00:41:05,580 --> 00:41:06,179
I've seen

914
00:41:06,180 --> 00:41:07,930
plenty of men like him in Chang'an.

915
00:41:08,100 --> 00:41:09,890
They are usually overlooked nobodies,

916
00:41:11,060 --> 00:41:12,059
but the moment they are

917
00:41:12,060 --> 00:41:13,690
given even a sliver of power,

918
00:41:14,140 --> 00:41:15,890
they turn into rabid mutts.

919
00:41:18,020 --> 00:41:20,139
Lately, he's been down at the docks,

920
00:41:20,140 --> 00:41:22,090
counting merchant ships.

921
00:41:23,100 --> 00:41:24,139
He has also looked into

922
00:41:24,140 --> 00:41:26,210
Lingnan's tax records from recent years.

923
00:41:27,820 --> 00:41:29,450
He trained in mathematics.

924
00:41:29,900 --> 00:41:32,850
He barely needs the numbers
before spotting something fishy.

925
00:41:33,300 --> 00:41:35,250
If he gets ahold of anything solid...

926
00:41:37,460 --> 00:41:38,970
I'm sure you wouldn't want

927
00:41:38,980 --> 00:41:40,179
a man like that

928
00:41:40,180 --> 00:41:41,530
sinking his teeth into you.

929
00:41:43,980 --> 00:41:46,490
It's just not worth the risk.

930
00:41:52,420 --> 00:41:54,170
You're telling me all this

931
00:41:57,700 --> 00:41:58,890
because you

932
00:42:01,340 --> 00:42:02,530
want to help me?

933
00:42:05,700 --> 00:42:07,379
I came to Lingnan on orders

934
00:42:07,380 --> 00:42:08,890
from the Right Chancellor.

935
00:42:09,180 --> 00:42:11,410
Your godfather has shown me
nothing but kindness.

936
00:42:11,980 --> 00:42:13,459
You're not an outsider.

937
00:42:13,460 --> 00:42:15,570
Of course I wouldn't turn a blind eye.

938
00:42:18,700 --> 00:42:21,890
Since you don't care for small talk,

939
00:42:22,300 --> 00:42:23,730
I'll take my leave.

940
00:42:24,380 --> 00:42:25,579
Before you arrived,

941
00:42:25,580 --> 00:42:27,610
I already ordered a few dishes.

942
00:42:28,980 --> 00:42:30,170
Please enjoy.

943
00:42:31,140 --> 00:42:32,330
Goodbye.

944
00:42:34,980 --> 00:42:38,219
=The Litchi Road=

945
00:42:38,220 --> 00:42:40,650
You and I should be comrades in arms.

946
00:42:42,100 --> 00:42:44,259
But, we both admire the same beauty.

947
00:42:44,260 --> 00:42:45,499
I missed my chance.

948
00:42:45,500 --> 00:42:46,699
But you still have yours.

949
00:42:46,700 --> 00:42:48,490
You have the talent?

950
00:42:48,740 --> 00:42:51,090
And the looks too?

951
00:42:55,140 --> 00:42:56,330
How shallow of me.

952
00:42:56,860 --> 00:42:58,210
Let me help you once more.

953
00:42:58,700 --> 00:43:01,050
I'll give you another push.

954
00:43:02,620 --> 00:43:03,810
You...

955
00:43:05,100 --> 00:43:06,290
Good news!

956
00:43:06,820 --> 00:43:07,699
Good news!

957
00:43:07,700 --> 00:43:09,250
Su?

958
00:43:21,240 --> 00:43:23,579
Although I cling to a branch
in Lingnan

959
00:43:23,580 --> 00:43:25,760
I'm popular

960
00:43:25,930 --> 00:43:28,439
My immortal aura drifted to Chang'an

961
00:43:28,440 --> 00:43:30,200
Driving people mad

962
00:43:30,630 --> 00:43:32,889
Who wore out their shoes for me

963
00:43:32,890 --> 00:43:35,420
Running around all day without rest

964
00:43:35,510 --> 00:43:37,679
Just to earn a sweet fruit to eat?

965
00:43:37,680 --> 00:43:39,810
Everyone wants
a taste of something new

966
00:43:40,230 --> 00:43:42,419
I stumble through mountains, rivers,
lakes, and seas

967
00:43:42,420 --> 00:43:44,820
In my dreams

968
00:43:44,950 --> 00:43:47,109
Endless deceit

969
00:43:47,110 --> 00:43:49,160
Absurd negotiation

970
00:43:49,750 --> 00:43:51,819
I also want to see
red tiles and golden bricks

971
00:43:51,820 --> 00:43:54,290
A prosperous world

972
00:43:54,480 --> 00:43:55,589
But all I see

973
00:43:55,590 --> 00:43:58,960
Is a man crying all night

974
00:43:58,980 --> 00:44:01,479
A little bit every day

975
00:44:01,480 --> 00:44:03,989
A little bit crazier

976
00:44:03,990 --> 00:44:07,640
I was once carefree in Lingnan,
only sharing the moonlight

977
00:44:07,880 --> 00:44:12,560
With heaven and earth

978
00:44:12,650 --> 00:44:17,409
I'm popular but with nowhere to rest

979
00:44:17,410 --> 00:44:21,940
I saw the greed of the world

980
00:44:22,160 --> 00:44:26,909
I was once carefree in Lingnan

981
00:44:26,910 --> 00:44:31,639
Only wishing to return
to the forest and dream

982
00:44:31,640 --> 00:44:36,750
Enjoy the breeze
and the crescent moon again

983
00:44:36,880 --> 00:44:41,630
Carefree and humble from then on

984
00:44:41,760 --> 00:44:44,129
A little bit every day

985
00:44:44,130 --> 00:44:46,529
A little bit crazier

986
00:44:46,530 --> 00:44:48,869
A little bit every day

987
00:44:48,870 --> 00:44:51,660
A day of insanity after another

988
00:45:15,030 --> 00:45:18,510
I was once carefree in Lingnan

989
00:45:19,080 --> 00:45:23,190
Swinging on green hills
and leafy branches

990
00:45:23,880 --> 00:45:29,040
One day we'll meet in Chang'an

991
00:45:29,230 --> 00:45:34,310
Embark on this crazy destiny
